## Overview

Fix three separate issues affecting the Kanban board and site navigation:
1. Kanban widget overflows behind AI sidebar at high zoom (110%+)
2. Missing edit/rearrange buttons on column headers
3. Page reloads when navigating to Notes/Kanban, causing Backup Modal to reappear

---

## Problem Statement

### Issue 1: Kanban Widget Overflow at High Zoom
When zooming past 110% with 7 columns, the Kanban board widget expands outward behind the AI sidebar instead of staying between both sidebars with horizontal scroll.

**Root Cause:** The `.kanban-board` container uses `overflow-x-auto` but lacks `max-width` constraint, so at high zoom the fixed column widths cause overflow behind the AI sidebar.

### Issue 2: Column Edit/Rearrange Buttons Missing
Column management (edit/rename/reorder) is only accessible through the Column Manager modal. Users want inline buttons directly on each column header for quick access.

**Root Cause:** Column headers only show color indicator, title, task count, and "+ Add task" button. No edit or drag UI.

### Issue 3: Page Reload on Navigation
The site reloads when navigating to Kanban and Notes pages, which causes the Backup Prompt Popup to reappear after closing it on the dashboard.

**Root Cause:** Migration code in Notes.tsx calls `window.location.reload()` on every mount (lines 634-658), and the Backup Modal's `hasChecked` flag is stored in component state (not sessionStorage), so it resets on reload.

