## Key Decisions

### 1. Remove Migration Code Instead of Fixing
**Reasoning:**
- Migration was one-time cleanup for corrupted Notes data
- All users who needed migration have already run it
- Keeping migration code causes ongoing UX issues (page reloads)
- No benefit to keeping it, only downsides

**Alternative Considered:** Move migration check to App.tsx with better guards
**Why Rejected:** Still adds unnecessary complexity for zero benefit

### 2. Use sessionStorage Instead of localStorage for Backup Modal
**Reasoning:**
- Backup Modal should only show once **per session**, not once **forever**
- sessionStorage persists across page navigations within same browser tab/session
- sessionStorage auto-clears when tab/browser closes (fresh session = fresh reminder)
- Matches user expectation: "I dismissed it this session, don't show again until I come back"

**Alternative Considered:** localStorage with timestamp
**Why Rejected:** Would require complex expiration logic, sessionStorage is simpler and matches intent

### 3. Add max-w-full Instead of Calculating Dynamic Max Width
**Reasoning:**
- Tailwind's `max-w-full` sets `max-width: 100%`, which naturally constrains to parent
- Simple, declarative solution (1 class)
- Works at all zoom levels and viewport sizes
- Horizontal scroll already implemented via `overflow-x-auto`

**Alternative Considered:** Calculate max-width based on sidebar widths with JavaScript
**Why Rejected:** Overly complex, brittle (breaks if sidebar widths change), CSS solution is better

### 4. Conditional Rendering of Edit Buttons Based on Prop
**Reasoning:**
- Only show edit buttons when `onEditColumn` callback is provided
- Allows KanbanColumn to be used elsewhere without edit UI
- Follows React best practices (controlled component pattern)
- Clean separation of concerns

**Alternative Considered:** Always show buttons
**Why Rejected:** Would break other uses of KanbanColumn, poor component design

### 5. Auto-Open Edit Form with useEffect Instead of Prop
**Reasoning:**
- ColumnManager already has edit form state (`editingColumn`, `formData`, `showAddForm`)
- useEffect watches `initialEditingColumnId` and triggers existing `handleEdit()` function
- Reuses existing logic, no duplication
- Declarative pattern: "When initialEditingColumnId changes, edit that column"

**Alternative Considered:** Pass pre-filled form data as prop
**Why Rejected:** Would bypass existing edit logic, duplicating state management

